\(\forall x \in \mathbb{R}_+^*, \text{Arctan} \, x + \text{Arctan} \, \frac{1}{x} =\frac{\pi}{2}\)<br><br>\(\forall x \in \mathbb{R}_-^*, \text{Arctan} \, x + \text{Arctan} \, \frac{1}{x} =-\frac{\pi}{2}\)<br><br>Preuve :<br>\(\begin{aligned}
g : \mathbb{R}_+^* &\to \left[-\frac{\pi}{2} , \frac{\pi}{2}\right]\\
x &\mapsto \text{Arctan} \, x + \text{Arctan} \, \frac{1}{x} 
\end{aligned}\)<br>\(g\) est dérivable sur \(\mathbb{R}_+^*\) par quotient, composition et somme :<br>\(g'(x) = \frac{1}{1+x^2} - \frac{1}{x^2} \cdot \text{Arctan}' \frac{1}{x} \)<br>\(= \frac{1}{1+x^2} - \frac{1}{x^2} \cdot \frac{1}{1+(\frac{1}{x})^2} \)<br>\(= \frac{1}{1+x^2} - \frac{1}{x^2+\frac{x^2}{x^2}}=\frac{1}{1+x^2} - \frac{1}{x^2+1}=0  \)<br>Ainsi, \(\forall x \in \mathbb{R}_+^*, g'(x) =0\), comme \(\mathbb{R}_+^*\) est un intervalle, \(\exists c \in \mathbb{R} ,  \, g(x)=c\)<br>En particulier, \(g(1)=c\) i.e. \(\text{Arctan} (1)+\text{Arctan}(\frac{1}{1})=c\)<br>i.e. \(\frac{\pi}{4} +\frac{\pi}{4} =c\)<br><br>d'où \(c= \frac{\pi}{2}\)<br><br>Ainsi, \(\forall x \in \mathbb{R}_+^*, \, \text{Arctan}(x)+\text{Arctan}(\frac{1}{x})= \frac{\pi}{2}\)
